meanings.definition: To surpass in gnawing or chewing.
meanings.sent1: The hungry squirrel outgnawed the other squirrels to get to the acorn first.
meanings.sent2: The beaver outgnawed the fallen tree to build its dam.
meanings.sent3: The little mouse outgnawed the big rat in a race to nibble through the cheese.
meanings.sent4: Her determination to succeed was like a tiny rodent that outgnawed through any obstacle in its path.
meanings.sent5: The termite outgnawed through the wooden door with incredible speed.

meanings.definition: To be gnawed more than something else.
meanings.sent1: The old bone was outgnawed by the new puppy in no time.
meanings.sent2: The rope was outgnawed by the persistent rat, causing it to break free.
meanings.sent3: The delicious treat was outgnawed by the mischievous dog when no one was looking.
meanings.sent4: His worries outgnawed at his mind like a relentless rodent chewing through a sack of grain.
meanings.sent5: The rust on the metal gate was outgnawed by time, slowly eating away at its strength.
